\f0\b0 \uc0\u55356 \u56812 \u55356 \u56807 
\f1\b On this day, Albert Einstein
\f2\b0  (1879-1955) died. He was a German-born theoretical physicist
\fs22\fsmilli11200 \cf4 \super  
\fs28 \cf2 \nosupersub who developed the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Theory_of_relativity"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 theory of relativity}}, one of the two pillars of modern physics (alongside {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quantum_mechanics"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 quantum mechanics}}). His work is also known for its influence on the philosophy of science. He is best known to the general public for his {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mass%E2%80%93energy_equivalence"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 mass\'96energy equivalence}} formula
\fs33 \cb1  E=mc\'882
\fs28 \cb3 , which has been dubbed "the world's most famous equation\'94. He received the 1921 {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nobel_Prize_in_Physics"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Nobel Prize in Physics}} "for his discovery of the law of the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Photoelectric_effect"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 photoelectric effect}}", a pivotal step in the development of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Introduction_to_quantum_mechanics"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 quantum theory}}.\cb1 \
\cb3 He published {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_scientific_publications_by_Albert_Einstein"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 more than 300 scientific papers}} and more than 150 non-scientific works. His intellectual achievements and originality have made the word "Einstein" synonymous with "genius". {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eugene_Wigner"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Eugene Wigner}} compared him to his contemporaries, writing that "Einstein's understanding was deeper even than{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_von_Neumann"}}{\fldrslt \cf4  von Neumann}}'s. His mind was both more penetrating and more original".
\fs22\fsmilli11200 \cf4 \super \
